The paper proposes a distributed learning scheme for updating the probability distribution of wind power forecast errors, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the problem of data collection and sharing among market participants, which involves distributed systems and networks, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely sub-category. The use of Gaussian mixture models and incremental learning strategies suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) are also relevant sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of uncertainty in wind power generation, which is a common problem in renewable energy systems, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
